Description: Fragment of shoulder of a closed vase, perhaps a hydria or oenochoe. Fine yellow-buff clay. Shoulder reserved with dull black line to the bottom; glazed above and below. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 456)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.774)
